tip.text: Icy popsicle on a hot day..  🍉 & 🍓

venue.name: 松阪牛焼肉M 法善寺横丁店

tip.text: Chinese restaurant near gion street. Food is just average. Indoor smoking. Gyoza is famous in this place but tasted average too.

venue.name: Nakatanidou (中谷堂 三条もちいどの店)

Both lobster and crab are serve as 'cold dish' in a good way, definitely a quick place to grab a bite.
This is one of the must to try out too, is scramble egg with fish soup. Very appetising and aromatic especially on a cooling evening.

location.neighborhood: Taman Tun Doktor Ismail, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: A must to order! One of the highlight of the day. Would go for tapas than paella..

contact.facebookName: Marta's Kitchen in KL Paella and Tapas

location.address: The Signature, 3 Jalan Sri Hartamas 22, Desa Sri Hartamas

location.address: T8 & T9, Third Floor, Atria Shopping Gallery

formattedAddress: T8 & T9, Third Floor, Atria Shopping Gallery (Lot T8 & T9, 3rd Floor)
location.address: T8 & T9, Third Floor, Atria Shopping Gallery

tip.text: Lemon curd of course.. The best...
Char siu bao and wu tao kao yeok a must try..
How often you notice any mix rice stall that serve mackerel fish roe... My damage is only rm8 ✌🏻️✌🏻✌🏻
The herbal jelly/kwai lin gou also one of the highlight. Night time the foreigner lady staff operating the stall dosant seems to understand english alot which twice serving me wrong food...
Friendly uncle that run the shop. Both chicken and siu yeok tasted pretty good too. Hardly any places that serve ginger together with chilly..

The highlight goes to pomelo salad. The taste combination is awesomely good.. It carry a strong fragrant from the leaf and dried shrimp. Thai ice tea a must try too.
Smoothie bowl has such a good presentation and of caz IG worthy.. Definitely a hidden gem in hartamas area

Have a break, have a waffle 🤓

Fresh river prawn fried noodle, size is as long as my index finger. Enough wok hei, noodle is very fragrant and absorb from the river prawn essence..

contact.facebookName: Teo Chew Yuen - Fine Teo Chew Cuisine

venue.name: 兴隆台湾面馆 Heng Long Taiwan Mee

location.address: Lot G110 Ground Floor, Bangsar Shopping Centre

Second best cendol after aunty koh. Fish ball rojak is abit disappointing. Dont bother trying that

venue.name: 有米氣 You MI Qi Restaurant

Average claypot rice, vege is overprice for the portion at rm8, liver sausage tasted normal and rice does not bring out the pungent from liver sausage oil. Overall is just average food place

location.address: 100-P2.041 & 043, Block J, The School, Jaya One

Price increased just shortly a year by 50 cents  :)
Did not reserved a spot and it was full hence requested to dine in only dessert at outside and it was granted :) loving the green tea macha home made ice cream with red bean paste.
Clams, chicken is one of the highly reco to try out.This place served pretty good chinese food and is cheap like what others reviewed.Dont bother on the oyster omelet,oyster is too puny and tasteless

Food is just above average and overrated. Boat noodle is relatively small portion but is expensive.
Gula melaka overload!
The instant noodle with herbalish soup and pork innards tasted awesome! Mango sticky rice and pandan flavor hot cake just above average

My every year first day of CNY place for dine in since they are open thru out the CNY period. Yam cake is still the bomb with friendly lady boss
90min aromatherapy massage for 950 baht. It has increased priced over the years and yet quality is still tip top.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10110

location.address: No. 23, Jalan Helang Sewah, Kepong Baru

3 different level of cheese, mild, medium and heavy flavor. Cheese tart tasted too mild, mini cheese tart cheesy moderate. Each person only allow to buy 3 mini's

venue.name: Choon Prawn Mee House 春虾面

Price for a bowl of laksa for year 2016 😀
Food is just average but price is on the high side. Could cost 20+ for local thai dishes. Do try out their thai ice tea too.

location.address: Ansa Kuala Lumpur (Lot 0.2), Jalan Bukit Bintang

tip.text: Decent mee siam comes with fried chicken..

venue.name: Kek Seng Coffee Shop (格成茶室)

CKT that comes with squid ring. Lacking in taste and 'wok hei'. chilly paste having abit after burn smell. Wouldnt reco to try out..

venue.name: Sin Hwa Coffee Shop (新華茶室)

tip.text: Tomyam instant noodle with add on fried fish roe is pretty good! Fried fish is fresh too but lacking in flour seasoning flavor.

venue.name: Jit Sheng Duck Rice (日昇香港烧鸭饭)

tip.text: Not bad for the cake selection and recommended to try out by one of their staff

Vietnam style pork rib noodle only available during weekend. A must try too
Rojak sotong and cendol of course. Friendly staff as well.
Cranky and lansi lady boss. This place is always full house but i recon they served one of the best claypot chicken rice in PJ.

venue.name: Restoran Ong Kee (安记芽菜鸡沙河粉 Tauge Ayam)

tip.text: Curry noodle served with coagulated pig blood. Certainly penang style.. One of the recommendation too. Give it a try

Cozy place for brunch. Sausage taste pretty good and so does the fluffy and flaky croissant

location.address: Block D-G-1, Encorp Strand Garden Office, Jalan PJU 5/1, Kota Damansara

Bak kut teh soup need to be consume hot, when it turn warm/cold, it tasted sugar sweet. Guess they either added sugar or sugarcane as their ingredient, definitely not pork bone kind of sweetness taste

venue.name: Restoran Lieong Kee Bae Good Teh (良记肉骨茶)

Surprisingly the food here tasted pretty good for 'cafe' concept. Roast pork curry noodle highly recommended to try out. Roast pork nasi lemak is not too bad too.. Give it a try..

formattedAddress: No. 72A Jalan Universiti, Jaya One (Ground Floor, The School)

tip.text: Buttermilk is just way too addictive and of course with the aroma from curry leaf with creamy buttery sauce

venue.name: Restaurant Wong Poh 旺来海鲜饭店

The shroom pizza 🍄🍄

location.address: Tropicana City Mall (Lot G39B & G39C), Jalan SS 20/27

Rm7.90 per piece. Enjoy while is freshly serve out from the oven. It is literally one bite and sent u to heaven..

formattedAddress: Lot SK7a second floor (1 Utama SC)

venue.name: 新桃园茶餐室 Sun Tho Yuen

Chilly gives such a kick ass flavor to the noodle.. Downside is their meatball i find it very soft and no 'bouncy' feeling at all
Decent place for YTF. Economy noodle and meehoon is rather tasteless..got to drizzle some soy sauce

venue.name: Klang Hin Leong Tyre Services Sdn Bhd

tip.text: Certainly the better version of cendol in PJ. Not skimpy in the ingredient too.
Seafood is totally not fresh, for the price you pay able to get a better quality buffet steamboat. First and the last time here!

The amount of prawn and cockles being serve for the price of rm6.50. Worth every penny.
Crispy fried prawn chee cheong fun and the siew mai the best.. Pork ribs is abit too tough to chew but flavor wise is not too bad. Chicken leg is such a disappointment due no strong 'fishy' taste

formattedAddress: Bangsar Shopping Center (Lot T109 & T111A, 3rd Floor)

venue.name: Kedah Asam Laksa at Taman Bahagia LRT

location.address: 逢甲路跟福星路交叉口

location.address: 捷運劍潭站1號出口左面

tip.text: Cheap affordable claypot chicken rice, only thing is the salted fish tasted less salted. Overall still worth a try

Decent place for shave ice dessert with friendly staff

tip.text: Worth a try for the mee sua, do remember to put abit of the chilly sauce to give some extra kick to your tastebud. It doesnt have oyster, just parsley and intestine

Good scenic view of the hot spring
Yummy trio color balls... Papaya milk is awesome too

Fantastic spot, scenic view
'Red tea stall' smelly toufu, egglet, grill scallop, trio color sweet potato ball a must try

tip.text: Fresh air but nothing much to do here.. Winding road. Go for the lavender and lemon grass ice cream. Choco mint and, rose ice cream and the mousse cake tasted pretty bad
Long queue for the cake. Best seller will be cheese flavor. Normal flavor is just similar to chiffon cake. Red bean cake with generous amount of fillings. Worth a try
Drinks menu is quite confusing. Lots of pricing here and there. Staff speaks moderate english. Overall the bubble tea is good. First bubble tea establishment in taiwan.

venue.name: 春水堂人文茶館 Chun Shui Tang Cultural Tea House

tip.text: Nice store concept. Do note u only can try 1 flavor although they serve 40 over flavors of ice creams
Decent place for local taiwanese dinner. Pork knuckle and pork rib is relatively good. Set meals comes with soup and rice
Surprisingly the food here isnt too bad. Fried rice and the side dishes satay is quite good
Fantastic soup lala, must to order too!!
Chinese nasi lemak another highlight to try out in this place. Sotong and sambal tasted heavenly
Less herbalish taste. Overall is just average for the soup base
Mix rice... Dont need to think twice what to eat. Cheap, affordable and good. This plate only cost me rm6!
This place is famous for clams and mussel. Highly recommended to order the large size as the smaller version is very little to satisfied the stomach. 🐚🐚
Char koay teow enough wok hei and taste awesome. Despite the place is relatively warm and the chef is always grumpy, would still order this again. Big bowl with 4 medium size prawns cost rm6.50
Live up to the food truck name, i would second that. Burger flavor is so much better than other ramli i have tried before surrounding pj.
Care for a bowl of late night porridge? Fried intestine is superb combining with a bowl of hot porridge.
Tried both, prefer eng ann popiah more than tan kee due to its flavor. Tan kee popiah has the best wax meat in it compare to eng ann but lack of certain flavor. My vote goes to eng ann(orange plate)

tip.text: The varieties of colorful nyonya kuih. They do sell the remnants of small little pieces mixture of kuih also for rm2.
Another day another bowl.. Yummy..
Highly recommended to order their sweet and sour pork.. Hardly can ever find such cooking style. Crispy on the outside despite the sauce has been pour on the meat. Mapo toufu is just average

venue.name: Mei Wei Little Kitchen Restaurant 美味小厨

tip.text: Short handed staff, parking issue, long queue, springy noodle, hot and stuffy and secullent char siew.
Waited only 15min for this bowl!!! Amazingly improve in time preparation!!! Perhaps the only less heavy traffic will be between 8-10am for short waiting time
Somehow my personal preference will be honeydew flavor compare to the normal kind. But among all the frogurt in town, my top choice still goes to llao llao

tip.text: Nowadays usually serve yee mee in normal bowl, surprisingly this place still practicing the old style way by using claypot!! Yummyy
Milk chocolate is so smooth and the brownie crepe actually balance the entire sweetness. Plate of this cost rm32
Tho the loh bak is just average but i would say the ah poh served the best yam cake in town during weekend.

tip.text: Affordable teow chew porridge. Dishes not as much choices compare to SS2 but price wise definitely cheaper
Queue for table 1 hour, food arrival take 1 hour too. So plan your time accordingly. Nestum mantis prawn and soup lala a must order. Parking is quite hassle here. Not to mention food is cheap!!
Website photo seems like 10 years ago. Hotel food is above average. Renggis island snorkeling is very nice. Beach has lots of rocks and dead corals. Sea is beautiful, clean and clear water
Top 10 CKT in klang valley, voted by the star. Their fried intestine porridge also a must try.

venue.name: Say Huat Restaurant (發中發飲食中心)

tip.text: They served the best hainanese pork chop ever. Op for the yam cake as well. Is highly reco to try

Decent bkt place in sec14 pj. Newly open restaurant. Soup base are more to herbalish type. Dry bkt they have added lots of cuttlefish.Pig stomach and intestine better go with dry type,flavorful enough
